                    <img src="~/Content/img/blockchain.png" alt="">
                    <b>The blockchain</b> — is the modern technology of record and storage of information working by the principle of the distributed database: information is copied and stored not on the centralized server, and on multimillion computers of the users who are logging in a blockchain. This technology has been created in 2009, together with cryptocurrency bitcoin. Her creator it is considered to be Satoshi Nakamoto, which nobody managed to reveal the personality still. The blockchain is public and at the same time protected. It is provided thanks to:
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <i></i>
                            To use of difficult algorithms;
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i></i>
                            To application of special cryptographic methods;
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i></i>
                            To work of thousands of computers which are switched on in a mining among which all volume of data is distributed.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <b>The blockchain</b> — network books regular independent audit and provides the highest extent of account and identification. Each happening transaction is coordinated with some time interval. All data are public. Now the blockchain, is generally used for transfers of cryptocurrencies. The technology provides full transparency and high speed of transactions. All translation process takes only a few minutes and costs ten times cheaper than bank. If you store money and information in a blockchain, records will never be lost or forged.
                </p>
                <p></p>
            </div>
